ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I honestly don't know if I would recommend the class. Someone could get just as much from reading Shakespeare on his or her own as I got from this seminar. We read Shakespeare plays, we didn't really talk about them or about the companion Jacobean plays, we moved right on to the next Shakespeare play we really didn't talk about, etc. The seminar just didn't do anything for me. It didn't help me get a better idea of the period, or familiarize me with new material, or open up Shakespeare to me in interesting ways, or show me the type of class I would one day like to teach. It's not a bad seminar, it's just not a great one either. You take it because you have to take it.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It was great to expand my knowledge of Jacobean drama NOT by Shakespeare (funny praise for a Shakespeare, course, but a valuable lesson).
